# App.jsx Guard

`src/renderer/src/App.jsx` is a legacy integration surface. Prefer not to add new feature logic there by default, but small routing edits are allowed when they are the clearest route.

Before editing `App.jsx`, read `docs/APP_JSX_CHANGE_MAP.md` and explain which single region you need to touch.

Prefer these routes:

- Component UI -> `src/renderer/src/components`
- Reusable controls -> `src/renderer/src/components/ui`
- Pure transforms and ranking/parsing logic -> `src/renderer/src/utils`
- Persisted defaults -> `src/renderer/src/config/defaultConfig.js`
- Main-process IO/export/download work -> `src/main` plus preload wiring
- Styling -> `src/renderer/src/index.css` or `src/renderer/src/styles`
- Copy -> `src/renderer/src/locales/*.json`

If `App.jsx` must change, keep the edit small, contiguous, and limited to routing, props, state wiring, or replacing one complete JSX block. Afterward run `npm run guard:app-jsx` and `npm run build`; the guard is a warning unless `STRICT_APP_JSX_GUARD=1` is set.
